            October 2024]</commencementNote><part startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852036_002" name="P1" temporalId="P1"><num value="1">Part 1</num><heading>Preliminary</heading><section startPeriod="2025-05-22" status="omitted" reason="omittedAsSpent" id="ID_1726025852051_003" name="s1" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><sourceNote>(Omitted as spent—<ref href="hk/2025/er1">E.R. 1 of 2025</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852067_004" name="s2" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Interpretation</heading><leadIn>In these Rules—</leadIn><def name="ConcessionaryPeriod"><term>concessionary period</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">寬減期</term>) means the period of 3 years beginning on the earliest date specified under <ref>section 32(2)</ref> of the Ordinance in relation to the Tribunal;</def><def name="Efee"><term>e-fee</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">電子費用</term>) means a fee that is payable under these Rules for an SCT-related matter that is carried out by means of an e-system;</def><def name="FeesRules"><term>Fees Rules</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">《費用規則》</term>) means the Small Claims Tribunal (Fees) Rules (<ref href="/hk/cap338B">Cap. 338 sub. leg. B</ref>);</def><def name="Registrar"><term>Registrar</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">司法常務官</term>) has the meaning given by <ref>section 2</ref> of the District Court Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap336">Cap. 336</ref>);</def><def name="Registry"><term>Registry</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">登記處</term>) means the registry of the Tribunal;</def><def name="SCTrelatedMatter"><term>SCT-related matter</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">審裁處相關事宜</term>) means—<paragraph id="ID_1726025852145_005" name="a" temporalId="s2_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>an act or matter that relates to a proceeding in the Tribunal; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1726025852145_006" name="b" temporalId="s2_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>a service, or other matter, made available or provided by the Tribunal, the Registry or an office of the Tribunal;</content></paragraph></def><def name="Tribunal"><term>Tribunal</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">審裁處</term>) means the Small Claims Tribunal established by <ref>section 3</ref> of the Small Claims Tribunal Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap338">Cap. 338</ref>).</def></section></part><part startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852161_007" name="P2" temporalId="P2"><num value="2">Part 2</num><heading>Application</heading><section startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852161_008" name="s3" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Application</heading><content>These Rules apply in relation to an SCT-related matter that is carried out by means of an e-system.</content></section></part><part startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852161_009" name="P3" temporalId="P3"><num value="3">Part 3</num><heading>e-fees Payable for Certain Proceedings in Tribunal</heading><section startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852176_010" name="s4" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>e-fees payable for Tribunal proceedings</heading><subsection id="ID_1726025852176_011" name="1" temporalId="s4_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><leadIn>Subject to subrule (2), the following e-fee is payable for an SCT-related matter described in column 2 (<b><i>relevant matter</i></b>)—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1726025852176_012" name="a" temporalId="s4_1_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>during a period other than the concessionary period—the SCT fee for the item that bears the item number specified in column 3 opposite to the relevant matter;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1726025852176_013" name="b" temporalId="s4_1_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>during the concessionary period—a fee of an amount equivalent to 80% of the SCT fee for the item that bears the item number specified in column 3 opposite to the relevant matter.</content></paragraph></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852192_014" name="2" temporalId="s4_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>No e-fee is payable for item 9 of the Schedule.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852192_015" name="3" temporalId="s4_3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content>In this rule, a reference to a column is a reference to a column of the Schedule.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852192_016" name="4" temporalId="s4_4"><num value="4">(4)</num><leadIn>In this rule—</leadIn><def name="SCTFee"><term>SCT fee</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">審裁處費用</term>), in relation to an item, means a fee specified or described for the item in the <ref>Schedule </ref>to the Fees Rules.</def></subsection></section><section startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852207_017" name="s5" temporalId="s5"><num value="5">5.</num><heading>e-fees payable for applications for certified copies of Hong Kong Judgments</heading><leadIn>The following e-fee is payable for an application under <ref>section 33(1)</ref> of the Mainland Judgments in Civil and Commercial Matters (Reciprocal Enforcement) Ordinance (<ref href="/hk/cap645">Cap. 645</ref>)—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1726025852207_018" name="a" temporalId="s5_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>during a period other than the concessionary period—the prescribed fee mentioned in <ref>section 33(2)(b)</ref> of that Ordinance;</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1726025852207_019" name="b" temporalId="s5_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>during the concessionary period—a fee of an amount equivalent to 80% of that prescribed fee.</content></paragraph></section></part><part startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852223_020" name="P4" temporalId="P4"><num value="4">Part 4</num><heading>Miscellaneous</heading><section startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852223_021" name="s6" temporalId="s6"><num value="6">6.</num><heading>Rounding rule for e-fees payable during concessionary period</heading><subsection id="ID_1726025852223_022" name="1" temporalId="s6_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>A concessionary fee that is less than $5 must be rounded to the nearest 10 cents.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852223_023" name="2" temporalId="s6_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>A concessionary fee that is $5 or more but less than $10 must be rounded to the nearest 50 cents.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852223_024" name="3" temporalId="s6_3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content>A concessionary fee that is $10 or more but less than $100 must be rounded to the nearest whole dollar.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852223_025" name="4" temporalId="s6_4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content>A concessionary fee that is $100 or more but less than $1,000 and is not a multiplier of $5 must be rounded to the nearest multiplier of $5.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852239_026" name="5" temporalId="s6_5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content>A concessionary fee that is $1,000 or more but less than $10,000 and is not a multiplier of $10 must be rounded to the nearest multiplier of $10.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852239_027" name="6" temporalId="s6_6"><num value="6">(6)</num><leadIn>In this rule—</leadIn><def name="ConcessionaryFee"><term>concessionary fee</term> (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">寬減費用</term>) means the e-fee payable under <ref>rule 4(1)(b)</ref> or <ref>5(b)</ref>.</def></subsection></section><section startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852239_028" name="s7" temporalId="s7"><num value="7">7.</num><heading>Specific fee payable instead of general fee</heading><content>If an e-fee is specified specifically for an SCT-related matter, that fee is payable in substitution for and not in addition to any other general e-fee that is also payable for the matter.</content></section><section startPeriod="2024-10-31T00:00:00" status="operational" reason="inEffect" id="ID_1726025852254_029" name="s8" temporalId="s8"><num value="8">8.</num><heading>Power of Registrar</heading><subsection id="ID_1726025852254_030" name="1" temporalId="s8_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>The Registrar may reduce, remit or defer payment of an e-fee as the Registrar considers appropriate in a particular case.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1726025852254_031" name="2" temporalId="s8_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>If the Registrar exercises the power under subrule (1), the Registrar must endorse on the relevant document a note of the reduction, remission or deferment and the reason for it.</content></subsection></section></part><schedule startPeriod="2024-10-31" status="operational" reason="inEffect" name="sch0" temporalId="sch0" id="ID_1726025852270_032"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap638I/s4">r. 4</ref>]</note><heading>Fees Specified or Described in <ref>Schedule </ref>to Fees
